(878,	'TBUS32023',	1,	'Introduction to Ethics and the Organisation',	'Describe business ethics. Arguments supporting and against business ethics. Describe corporate social responsibility. Describe Kohlberg\'s Three Levels of Moral Development',	'2026-05-29 07:40:30'),
(879,	'TBUS32023',	2,	'Decision-making and moral dilemmas',	'The role of ethical theories. Describe the major normative theories i.e. Egoism, Utilitarianism, Ethics of Duties, Rights and Justice. Describe and illustrate moral dilemmas. Apply ethical theories to resolve ethical dilemmas',	'2026-05-29 07:40:30'),
(880,	'TBUS32023',	3,	'CSR and sustainability',	'Distinguish the various concepts of CSR. Present the stakeholder theory of the firm. Outline the concept of corporate accountability. Accounting & Finance - Corruption, Auditing, Sarbanes Oxley. Explain the basic forms of ethical misconduct when selling financial products. Explain the main arguments against insider trading and the challenges in applying these theories. Analyze the ethical issues raised by various hostile takeover tactics. Analyze the ethical issues affecting Accountants. Arguments for ethical investing',	'2026-05-29 07:40:30'),
(881,	'TBUS32023',	4,	'Human Resources - Bullying, Well Being, Rewards',	'Core ethical topics of employees\' rights and duties. The duties of employees and the company\'s involvement in enabling employees to live up to their duties. Basic issues and problems of managing employees in the context of globalization. The implication of sustainability for workplaces and for specific working conditions.',	'2026-05-29 07:40:30'),
(882,	'TBUS32023',	5,	'Mid-term Exam',	NULL,	'2026-05-29 07:40:30'),
(883,	'TBUS32023',	6,	'Operations - CSR, Waste, Procurement, Health & Safety',	'Describe the ethical issues and problems that arise in an organisation\'s dealings with its suppliers and competitors. Discuss whether corporations should assume some degree of extended responsibility for the ethics of their suppliers (bribery, misrepresentation, fair trade). Assess the arguments suggesting that attention to business interrelationships and the network economy may contribute to more sustainable business models (improved safety and reduction in waste)',	'2026-05-29 07:40:30'),
(884,	'TBUS32023',	7,	'Sales - Bribery, Misrepresentation, Fair Trade',	'Outline the ethical issues and problems faced in business-consumer relations. Develop notion of corporate citizenship in relation to consumers. Discuss the three conditions for voluntary exchange between the buyer and seller',	'2026-05-29 07:40:30'),
(885,	'TBUS32023',	8,	'Leadership Corruption, Toxicity',	'Describe the role of top management and Board of Directors. Outline corporate governance, disclosure, and executive compensation. Describe the ethical issues and problems that arise in an organisation\'s dealings with its suppliers and competitors. Outline the issues in recycling.',	'2026-05-29 07:40:30'),
(886,	'TBUS32023',	9,	'Marketing - Branding, Consumerism',	'Examine issues in context of globalization. Arguments for more responsible marketing practices. Ethical issues relating to marketing and the consumer in the areas of marketing management, marketing strategy and marketing research.',	'2026-05-29 07:40:30'),
(887,	'TBUS32023',	10,	'Corporate Governance',	'Describe Corporate Governance. Describe Corporate Disclosure. Explain Executive Compensation',	'2026-05-29 07:40:30'),
(888,	'TBUS32023',	11,	'Final Exam',	NULL,	'2026-05-29 07:40:30'),
